<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-534-272  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 534 272.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Journal of Systems and Software  July 1989 v10 n1 p23(6).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Object-oriented graphical information systems: research plan andevaluation metrics.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Moreau, Dennis R.; Dominick, Wayne D.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The object-oriented design strategy, as both a problemdecomposition and a system-implementation methodology, holdssignificant potential benefits for software design andimplementation in scientific computing environments.andO;Additionally, certain characteristics of object-oriented systemsare particularly suited to supporting graphics-applicationdevelopment.andP;  This paper presents the initial direction andorganization of research and development activities in the area ofobject-oriented graphical information systems at the University ofSouthwestern Louisiana.andP;  These activities, structured as afour-phase research plan, are intended to provide significant andextensible results in the evaluation of the impact ofobject-oriented methodologies on graphical-information systemdesign and implementation.andP;  The long-term goals of this researchinclude the formulation of complexity models for object-orienteddevelopment of software and the formulation and validation ofsoftware-development metrics appropriate to object-orientedsystems.andP;  (Reprinted by permission of the publisher.)andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Object-Oriented ProgrammingSoftware DesignGraphics SoftwareSouthwestern Louisiana, University ofProgram Development TechniquesData Base DesignSoftware Metrics.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>